   420	
   421	   The narrowest unsafe window — orphaned `ready` proposals not
   422	   yet referenced by a submitted plan task — exists between
   423	   Phase 2 and Phase 3. If Phase 3 fails after Phase 2 succeeded
   424	   for at least one proposal, the orchestrator could in principle
   425	   dispatch implement tasks for ready-but-unreferenced proposals.
   426	   We accept this narrow window for the reference impl,
   427	   documented as a known limitation; the spec-level fix
   428	   (atomic ready-and-submit) is out of scope for Phase 9 chunk 1
   429	   and applies equally to the existing scripted planner host.
   430	   The error page on Phase-3 failure surfaces the orphaned
   431	   proposal IDs explicitly so an operator can manually reclaim
   432	   the plan task and let the orchestrator re-dispatch a fresh
   433	   plan attempt.
   434	4. **Submit error** (`POST /planner/{task_id}/submit?status=error`):
   435	   - CSRF check.
   436	   - `store.submit(task_id, token, PlanSubmission(status="error"))`.
   437	   - No proposals are written.
   438	   - Drop the token. Render `planner_submitted.html`.
   439	5. **Reclaim path on expired/invalid claim token.** If any
   440	   `store.claim` / `store.submit` raises
   441	   `eden://error/invalid-claim-token` or
   442	   `eden://error/conflict` (e.g. another worker already claimed
   443	   after expiry), the form re-renders the planner list with a
   444	   banner naming the canonical error type and offering "claim
   445	   again." Field input is preserved across the re-render so the
   446	   user does not lose work-in-progress.
   447	6. **Errors** at any other point: re-render the form with
   448	   field-level messages; do not lose user input.
