   520	10. The `reference/README.md` web-ui row reflects the new status;
   521	    no stale "(not yet started)" text.
   522	
   523	## Execution order
   524	
   525	1. Scaffold `reference/services/web-ui/` (pyproject, package skeleton,
   526	   README stub, empty test files).
   527	2. Wire it into `uv sync`; confirm `uv run pyright` and
   528	   `uv run pytest -q` still green with the empty package.
   529	3. Build `make_app` and the index route; commit-equivalent
   530	   checkpoint.
   531	4. Build the planner routes against `InMemoryStore` with `TestClient`
   532	   covering each route in isolation.
   533	5. Build the templates and CSS; verify the unit tests still green
   534	   (templates render).
   535	6. Add `tests/test_planner_flow.py` covering the full claim →
   536	   submit happy path against `make_app`.
   537	7. Add the subprocess `pytest.mark.e2e` test, reusing
   538	   `_read_port_announcement` and the SIGTERM teardown helpers from
   539	   `reference/services/orchestrator/tests/test_e2e.py`. The UI
   540	   service announces `EDEN_WEB_UI_LISTENING host=… port=…` on stdout
   541	   on bind, mirroring the task-store-server convention.
   542	8. Documentation pass: `web-ui/README.md`, `reference/README.md`,
   543	   `AGENTS.md`, `docs/roadmap.md`.
   544	9. Local verification (every step in the Verification section).
   545	10. `/codex-review` on the implementation; iterate to convergence.
   546	11. PR, CI green, squash-merge.
   547	
   548	## Risks
   549	
   550	- **Stranded human claims.** A user who claims a plan task and
   551	  closes the tab leaves the claim token only in their session
   552	  cookie. Mitigation: the UI sets an explicit
   553	  `expires_at = now + --claim-ttl-seconds` on every claim, so the
   554	  task-store's `expired` reclaim cause picks abandoned claims back
   555	  up automatically (spec/v0/04-task-protocol.md §5). Phase 9e adds
   556	  an explicit operator-reclaim button as a faster recovery path.
   557	  The UI must not retry claims server-side for a user who doesn't
   558	  return — that would mask the issue.
   559	- **Partial proposal writes.** The Phase 1 → Phase 2 → Phase 3
   560	  ordering in §C narrows the unsafe window to "ready proposals
   561	  not yet referenced by a submitted plan task," but does not
   562	  eliminate it. A spec-level fix (atomic `mark_ready_and_submit`)
   563	  is out of scope for Phase 9 chunk 1; the implementation
   564	  surfaces orphaned proposal IDs to the operator on Phase-3
   565	  failure so they can reclaim and retry.
   566	- **Experiment-config drift.** The UI loads its own copy of
   567	  `experiment-config.yaml`; if it diverges from the
   568	  task-store-server's copy, planner-side validation could pass on
   569	  inputs the evaluator's metrics_schema would later reject. Phase
   570	  12's control plane is the right fix; for now the start-up
   571	  `experiment_id` mismatch check catches the loud cases.
   572	- **CSRF / cookie attribute regressions.** The cookie/CSRF policy
   573	  is enforced by `tests/test_security_invariants.py`. Any change
   574	  that loosens an attribute or skips the CSRF check breaks the
   575	  test, by design.
   576	- **Bearer-token leak via templating.** Mitigated by the
   577	  bearer-leak unit test, the JSON-line log redaction, and the
   578	  manual `grep -r "$EDEN_SHARED_TOKEN"` verification step. A
   579	  reviewer should still spot-check any new template that
   580	  receives the configuration object.
   581	- **`itsdangerous` session-secret rotation.** Out of scope for this
   582	  chunk; restarting the service with a different `--session-secret`
   583	  invalidates outstanding sessions, which is the documented
   584	  behavior. A real auth phase replaces this anyway.
   585	- **Vendored HTMX bit-rot.** Pin the version in `pyproject.toml`
   586	  comments and check the SHA-256 in `web-ui/README.md`; bumping is a
   587	  one-line follow-up but not silent.
   588	- **HTMX surprises.** If a partial-update interaction turns out to
   589	  need a feature HTMX doesn't cleanly support, fall back to
   590	  full-page submits for that flow rather than reaching for a JS
   591	  framework. The CSS is already a single file; the templates degrade
   592	  gracefully.
   593	- **Test scope creep.** The existing Phase 8b e2e test takes ~3
   594	  seconds because it forks five processes. Adding a second e2e test
   595	  that forks two more (task-store + UI) keeps it on the order of
   596	  another ~3 seconds; this is acceptable. If e2e total exceeds
   597	  ~30 seconds we revisit consolidating, but not preemptively.
   598	- **Reviewers' default expectation of a SPA.** The "Tech stack —
   599	  decision and alternatives considered" section is deliberately
   600	  detailed precisely because reviewers may default to "modern means
   601	  React." The codex-review should specifically scrutinize that
   602	  decision.

